---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Patriotometer" description="How the Patriotometer works, and why it exists.">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <a href="/" class="text-sm hover:underline" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">&larr; Back to quiz</a>

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-6 mb-6">About the Patriotometer</h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        I got tired of every political quiz sorting people into two buckets. Left or right. Red or blue.
        As if 330 million people fit neatly into a coin flip.
      </p>

      <p>
        The Patriotometer scores you across five axes — economic, social, authority, nationalism, and
        pragmatism — then maps you to one of eight archetypes. None of them are flattering. All of them
        are recognizable.
      </p>

      <p>
        The real fun is the lenses. Once you get your result, you can see how eight different groups
        would describe you — from your boomer uncle to a college freshman to an NPR listener.
        Everyone gets roasted. Nobody is safe.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8">How scoring works</h2>

      <p>
        Each question maps to one of five political axes. Your slider position (0–100) is normalized,
        then averaged per axis. The resulting five-dimensional score is compared against predefined
        ranges for each archetype. The archetype whose range best fits your scores wins.
      </p>

      <p>
        There's no "correct" result. The archetypes are descriptive stereotypes, not clinical assessments.
        If you don't like your result, the problem is you, not the algorithm.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8">This is satire</h2>

      <p>
        The Patriotometer is not a political assessment tool. It's not a scientific instrument. It's a
        mirror with a sense of humor. The vignettes are written to be sharp, funny, and equal-opportunity
        in their mockery. If your group didn't get roasted hard enough, that's a bug — not a bias.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8">Privacy</h2>

      <p>
        The quiz runs entirely in your browser. No data is collected, stored, or transmitted. Your
        answers never leave your device. There is no database, no analytics tracking your responses,
        no account to create.
        <a href="/privacy" class="underline" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Full privacy policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8">Built by</h2>

      <p>
        Made by <a href="https://centricle.com" class="underline" style="color: var(--color-accent);">ksmith</a>.
        No ads. No sponsored content. No data collection. Just a quiz that makes fun of everyone equally.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
